data.event: Mayor Don Pohlman was last reelected in April 2014.
Plymouth was surveyed in 1835 by United States Engineers.

event.title: was sold to Law on August 13, 1836

data.event: It was sold to Law on August 13, 1836.
Settlers continued trickling in and the town was organized on April 3, 1849.
The town was named Plymouth, after Plymouth, Massachusetts, where the Pilgrims had landed in 1620.
